EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO MOTOR AND OTHER VEHICLES -- MOTOR VEHICLE OFFENSES
***
1 This act would prohibit the division of motor vehicles from recording a moving violation
2 on a motorist's driving record, if the moving violation is one that can be paid by mail and is paid,
3 in full, by the motorist within thirty (30) days of its issuance; provided that, this procedure cannot
4 be utilized more than twice in one year.
5 This act would take effect upon passage.
